President Uhuru Kenyatta and DP William Ruto skipped the burial of veteran politician John Keen, which was attended by key opposition politicians. Uhuru and Ruto were represented by Interior CS Joseph Nkaissery (pictured), who passed on their tribute to Keen.Nkaissery said the Jubilee administration had taken an oath to protect the lives and property of Kenyans and those who break the law must be punished.&ldquo;The government will ensure that the election is credible. And that&rsquo;s the message from the President,&rdquo; Nkaissery told the mourners.Opposition leaders led by Raila Odinga hit at the government and accused Jubilee of failing to implement the Truth, Justice and Reconciliation Commission report. Keen, a former Cabinet minister, died on December 25 at the age of 90. He fought for the rights of marginalised people.